The USER function (of any name to choose)
give a real value to the FINAL ORDINATE of the POINT
of initial coordinates x,y,z.

This function has to have 3 parameters X Y Z in this order
and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized when the function is executed
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of this function ORDINATE.
           
EXAMPLE:
deffunc ORDINATE( x , y , z ) ; 
   if    (1<=x) et (x<100)
   then  ORDINATE = exp(x) ;
   else  ORDINATE =  x**2 +y -z ;
   endif;  
endfunc; 
